INDIAN spinal surgery experts from Spine Clinic India, Dr Viral Shah, Dr Ritesh Patel and his team, are expected in the country this week for conducting an initial screening camp for people with spine-related problems like neck pain, spine pain and sciatica issues. According to a statement from Regency Medical Centre in Dar es Salaam where the two days camp will be held on June 21 and 22, the specialists will also screen various spinal cord problems requiring surgical intervention. The statement said the two day camp is conducted in the government’s Public-Private Partnership spirit, as well as to reduce medical referrals abroad, to save the country’s forex. It said the camp is organized by Regency Medical Centre in collaboration with Lions Club of Dar es Salaam (Host) . The statement said experts will undertake consultation on neck pain, back pain spinal surgical procedures and spinal cord problems. It added that experts will select patients for major and minor spinal; surgical procedures which will be carried out at Regency Medical Centre. “This spinal screening and spinal surgical procedure camp will take place on 21st and 22nd June at Regency Hospital. This is a golden opportunity for fellow Tanzanians to avail this opportunity of getting treatment, including surgical procedures at the door steps of Regency Medical Centre in Dar es Salaam,” the statement said.